> Because of how well red kidney beans hold their shape during cooking they're perfect
> for simmered dishes like this one. This veggie curry is filled with protein, fibre
> and of course, plenty of flavour.

== Rice ==

Add @rice{150%grams} and @salt{to taste} to a #medium pot{} with a tight-fitting #lid{}.

Stir in the rice and bring to the boil.

Once boiling, lower the heat to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pot from the heat (still covered) and
leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will
continue to cook in its own steam).

== Curry ==

Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(peeled and chopped into small pieces).

Trim @cucumber{1/2}(quartered lengthways and chopped widthways into small pieces).

Roughly chop the @coriander{5%grams}(roughly chopped, stalks and all).

Quarter the @lemon{1/2}.

Drain and rinse the @red kidney beans{1%pack} in a #sieve{}. Mash half with a #fork{}.

Place a #large pot{} over medium-high heat with @butter{1%tbsp}.

When hot, add half the chopped onion and fry for ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add the @North Indian style spice mix{1%sachet} and fry for ~{1%minute}.

Pour in the @chopped tomatoes with onion & garlic{1%pack} and beans (both mashed and
whole).

Cover and simmer for ~{10-12%minutes}. Add the @garam masala{1%sachet} when the curry
has 2 mins left to simmer.

== Cucumber and Coriander Salad ==

Meanwhile, in a #bowl{} mix the chopped cucumber, remaining chopped onion and half the
coriander.

Season to taste with @salt{to taste}, @pepper{to taste} and lemon juice.

== Final Assembly ==

Stir half the @creme fraiche{125%grams} into the curry and allow to warm through.

Season to taste with @salt{to taste}, @pepper{to taste} and @sugar{to taste}.

Add a splash of @water{to taste} to loosen the curry if required.

Divide the curry between #bowls{} with spoonfuls of fluffy rice.

Squeeze over remaining lemon juice to taste.

Top with remaining coriander and creme fraiche.

Serve with cucumber salad alongside.